Ad Text:
The Company:

A leading Australian brand is looking for a PowerBI Developer contractor to work on business critical initiatives within their enterprise environment. You must be Sydney based and able to work in the office 3 days per week. This role is for an initial 6 months with the potential to be extended.

The Role:


Strong stakeholder engagement, with the ability to communicate with both non-technical and technical stakeholders including taking requirements and translating into Power BI solutions.
Develop PowerBI dashboards from business requirements and functional design documents, end user manuals and business glossaries.
Regular and effective internal customer engagement to build strong partnerships with stakeholders.
Collaboration with business units and cross-functional teams responsible for IT delivery and services.
Support the Data & Analytics Teams to build positive working relationships with stakeholders and promote leveraging BI solutions to assist with decision making.
Your Skillset:
 

5+ years of experience in building PowerBI dashboards and reports from scratch, ideally within a fast-paced enterprise environment.
Strong story-telling experience and design using PowerBI.
Customer / Stakeholder engagement & providing solutions through Business Intelligence.
DAX & SQL, Tabular Models.
Advanced PowerBI model optimisation using a variety of tools such as Dax Studio, ALM, Tabular Editor, etc. 
Strong knowledge of Data Warehousing concepts.
You must have unlimited working rights to be considered and be Sydney based.
